{"lemma":"رَحْب","slug":"رَحْب","root":"ر.ح.ب","root_slug":"ر-ح-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ح-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15020","","n15021","n15022","n15023"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%A8"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be wide, to be spacious, to be roomy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to welcome, to make welcome, to receive graciously"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"wide, spacious, roomy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَحُبَ (raḥuba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wideness, spaciousness, vastness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَحِبَ (raḥiba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wideness, spaciousness, vastness"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Ge'ez ርሑብ (rəḥub), Hebrew רָחַב (racháv, “to be wide”).\n\nCompare Ugaritic 𐎗𐎈𐎁 (rḥb), Hebrew רָחָב (rāḥāḇ) and Ge'ez ርሑብ (rəḥub)."},"ipa":["/ra.ħi.ba/","/ra.ħu.ba/","/raħ.ħa.ba/","/raħb/","/ruħb/","/ra.ħab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15020","headword_ar":"رَحُبَ","root":"rHb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) said of a place, (Msb,) or of a thing, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHubato","text_ar":"رَحُبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a land, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroD","text_ar":"اَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", S,) or of a country, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bilaAd","text_ar":"بِلَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":", A, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruHobN","text_ar":"رُحْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHaAbapN","text_ar":"رَحَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHiba","text_ar":"رَحِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHibato","text_ar":"رَحِبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHabN","text_ar":"رَحَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArHb","text_ar":"ارحب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArHbt","text_ar":"ارحبت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was, or became, ample, spacious, wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roomy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHubati Ald~aAru","text_ar":"رَحُبَتِ الدَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroHabat","text_ar":"اَرْحَبَت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify the same, i.e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, was ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, be ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (S, TA.) And they said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka waTul~ato","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ وَطُلَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroHabato","text_ar":"اَرْحَبَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the country,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbilaAdu","text_ar":"البِلَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be spacious to thee, and be moistened by gentle rain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by dew:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so accord. to Aboo-Is-hák. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAqato Ealayohimu AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"ضَاقَتْ عَلَيْهِمُ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA raHubato","text_ar":"بِمَا رَحُبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur ix. 119, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The earth became strait to them with"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"notwithstanding"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its spaciousness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHuba","text_ar":"رَحُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the original usage, is trans. by means of a particle; so that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHuba bika AlmakaAnu","text_ar":"رَحُبَ بِكَ المَكَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may the place be, spacious with thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: afterwards, by reason of frequency of usage, it became trans. by itself; and thus one said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHubatoka Ald~aAru","text_ar":"رَحُبَتْكَ الدَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, be, spacious with thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  [Hence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araHubakumu Ald~uxuwlu fiY TaAEatihi","text_ar":"اَرَحُبَكُمُ الدُّخُولُ فِى طَاعَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Was it proper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allowable, for you"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to enter among his obeyers?"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to become obedient to him?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K * TA:) referring to El-Kirmánee, (so in the S,) or Ibn-El-Kirmánee: (so in the TA:) mentioned by Kh, on the authority of Nasr Ibn-Seiyár; but he says, (S,) the verb thus used is anomalous; (S, K;) for a verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEula","text_ar":"فَعُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not trans., (K, TA,) accord. to the grammarians, (TA,) except with the tribe of Hudheyl, who, accord. to AAF, make it trans. (K, TA) when its meaning admits of its being so: (TA:) Kh mentions the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHubatokumu Ald~aAru","text_ar":"رَحُبَتْكُمُ الدَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, be, spacious with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but it is thought that there is an ellipsis here, and that it is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHubato bikumu Ald~aAru","text_ar":"رَحُبَتْ بِكُمُ الدَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and ElJelál Es-Suyootee mentions, on the authority of AAF, the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHuba A@ll~`hu jawofahu","text_ar":"رَحُبَ ا@للّٰهُ جَوْفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"was~aEahu","text_ar":"وَسَّعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make wide his belly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [J says, app. quoting Kh,] there is no sound verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEula","text_ar":"فَعُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is trans. except this; but as to the unsound, there is a difference of opinion: accord. to Ks,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qulotuhu","text_ar":"قُلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawulotuhu","text_ar":"قَوُلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but Sb says that this is not allowable, because it is trans.: (S:) Az says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHubatokumo","text_ar":"رَحُبَتْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not held to be allowable by the grammarians; and that Nasr is not an [approved] evidence. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n15021","headword_ar":"رَحْبٌ","root":"rHb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHiybN","text_ar":"رَحِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruHaAbN","text_ar":"رُحَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ample, spacious, wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roomy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) applied to a place, (Msb,) or a thing. (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biladN raHobN","text_ar":"بِلَدٌ رَحْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN raHobapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ رَحْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spacious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide, country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArD raHiybapN","text_ar":"ارض رَحِيبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manozilN raHobN","text_ar":"مَنْزِلٌ رَحْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHiybN","text_ar":"رَحِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spacious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide, place of alighting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN raHobN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ رَحْبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wide road."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidorN ruHaAbN","text_ar":"قِدْرٌ رُحَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ample cookingpot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruHaAbN","text_ar":"رُحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone is [elliptically] used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cooking-pot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 721.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN ruHaAbN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ رُحَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide in respect of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroj","text_ar":"فَرْج"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TK.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljawofi","text_ar":"الجَوْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHiybu","text_ar":"رَحِيبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide, in the belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, as mentioned by Es-Suyootee, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great eater; voracious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHiybN","text_ar":"رَحِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone. (S, K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN raHobu AlS~ador","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ رَحْبُ الصَّدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~adori","text_ar":"الصَّدْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruHobu","text_ar":"رُحْبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~adori","text_ar":"الصَّدْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHiybu","text_ar":"رَحِيبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dilated, in the breast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bosom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free-minded; free from distress of mind; without care:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from narrowness of mind; liberal, munificent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHobu Al*~iraAEi","text_ar":"رَحْبُ الذِّرَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Liberal, munificent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHobu AlbaAEi","text_ar":"رَحْبُ البَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~iraAEi","text_ar":"الذِّرَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHiybu","text_ar":"رَحِيبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAEi","text_ar":"البَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHobu Al*~iraAEi","text_ar":"رَحْبُ الذِّرَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extensive, power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength, in cases of difficulty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in the present art.:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having ample strength, and power, and might in war"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fight, courage, valour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prowess."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rE","text_ar":"ذرع"},{"kind":"text","text":") And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN raHobu Al*~iraAEi lika*aA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ رَحْبُ الذِّرَاعِ لِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability, for that."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHabapN","text_ar":"رَحَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n15022","headword_ar":"رُحْبٌ","root":"rHb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHuba","text_ar":"رَحُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q.v.]. (S, Msb, K.) [Used as a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ampleness, spaciousness, wideness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roominess."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S A, Mgh, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEaAhu A_ilaY Alr~uHobi","text_ar":"دَعَاهُ اـِلَى الرُّحْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He invited him to ampleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (A.) And hence the saying of Zeyd Ibn-Thábit to 'Omar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`hunaA biAlr~uHobi","text_ar":"هٰهُنَا بِالرُّحْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Advance to ampleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Mgh.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroHabN","text_ar":"مَرْحَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  [It is also used as an epithet:] see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n15023","headword_ar":"رَحَبٌ","root":"rHb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next following paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}